Just an FYI, I believe you guys are using the Apache HttpClient (Commons HTTP) to establish the connection to Bugzilla.  If so, I'm doing the same thing in one of my applications and in order to have the requests work, I had to do the following:

HttpClient client = HttpConfigurator.getConfiguredHttpClient(HttpVersion.HTTP_1_1, 15000, "UTF-8", 15000);
GetMethod getMethod = new GetMethod("<Bugzilla URL>/<ScriptName>");
NameValuePair[] bugData = {
    new NameValuePair("Bugzilla_login", loginName),
    new NameValuePair("Bugzilla_password", loginPassword),
    new NameValuePair(PRODUCT, productName),
    new NameValuePair(VERSION, productVersion),
    ...
};
getMethod.setQueryString(bugData);
client.executeMethod(getMethod);

As you'll see, the login name and password are passed in with the NameValuePairs for each request.  I have not looked at the Mylyn code to see how it's done by you guys, but thought I would share the above.  I hope it's useful.
